> ... except: the info returned using `vim.pack.get()` does not return a "src =" as part of the spec. This causes `vim.pack.update()` without specifying any plugins to fail because of the nil src entry.

I can not reproduce. Works for me with the following:
- `git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/nvim-mini/mini.nvim` when inside '/home/user/repos' directory.
- Use 'init.lua' with only `vim.pack.add({ 'file:///home/evgeni/repos/mini.nvim' })` call.
- Start Nvim and confirm install. Here is the output of `:=vim.pack.get()`:

    ```lua
    { {
        active = true,
        branches = { "main" },
        path = "/home/evgeni/.local/share/nvim-pack-demo/site/pack/core/opt/mini.nvim",
        rev = "61a5d44",
        spec = {
          name = "mini.nvim",
          src = "file:///home/user/repos/mini.nvim"
        },
        tags = {}
      } }
    ```

There is also the fact that all `vim.pack.get()` tets use 'file://' sources. And tests pass.
